    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you create a material, you define a collection of visual attributes and their options, which you can then reuse for multiple geometries in a scene."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A material has several visual properties, each of which defines a different part of SceneKitâ€™s lighting and shading process. Each visual property is an instance of the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnmaterialproperty"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class that provides a solid color, texture, or other 2D content for that aspect of SceneKitâ€™s rendering. The materialâ€™s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnmaterial/1462518-lightingmodelname"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property then determines the formula SceneKit uses to combine the visual properties with the lights in the scene to produce the final color for each pixel in the rendered scene. For more details on the rendering process, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnlightingmodel"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You attach one or more materials to an instance of the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometry"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class using its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometry/1523485-firstmaterial"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometry/1523472-materials"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. Multiple geometries can reference the same material. In this case, changing the attributes of the material changes the appearance of every geometry that uses it."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
